						<summary>

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1177, Rākshasa, Āshāḍha, śu. 11, Sōmavāra.</hi> The date is irregular; śu. 11 of Āshāḍha in Rākshasa corresponded to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1255 June 17 Thursday,</hi> not Monday, in the reign of the Yādava king <hi rend="bold">Kanharadēva. Kaṁhārashaṇaṅgidēva,</hi> the chief of <hi rend="bold">Mahāghāṭa,</hi> is said to have made a grant of land at <hi rend="bold">Nagarūru</hi> to the <hi rend="italic">chhatra</hi> (feeding house) attached to the temple of the god Sōmanātha.</p>						

						</summary>
